card_collections.mcmobs.name: Minecraft Mobs
card_collections.mcmobs.author: MinecraftWiki, skydarkchen
card.mcmobs.bat.name: Bat
card.mcmobs.bat.desc: A bat is a flying ambient passive mob that spawns in dark areas underground.
card.mcmobs.chicken.name: Chicken
card.mcmobs.chicken.desc: Chickens are common passive mobs found in most grassy biomes, and are the main source of chicken, feathers and eggs.
card.mcmobs.cod.name: Cod
card.mcmobs.cod.desc: Cod are common passive aquatic mobs found in oceans.
card.mcmobs.cow.name: Cow
card.mcmobs.cow.desc: A cow is a common passive mob and a source of leather, beef and milk. Cows are found in most grassy biomes.
card.mcmobs.donkey.name: Donkey
card.mcmobs.donkey.desc: Donkeys are variants of horses that, when tamed, can be ridden and equipped with chests.
card.mcmobs.horse.name: Horse
card.mcmobs.horse.desc: Horses are passive mobs that can be ridden when tamed.
card.mcmobs.pig.name: Pig
card.mcmobs.pig.desc: A pig is a common passive mob found in most grassy biomes. Pigs are a source of porkchops and can be equipped with a saddle to be driven.
card.mcmobs.piglin_baby.name: Piglin (baby)
card.mcmobs.piglin_baby.desc: A piglin is a neutral mob found in the Nether. They attack players on sight unless the player is equipped with at least one piece of golden armor. Players can use gold ingots to barter with them for various items.
card.mcmobs.pufferfish.name: Pufferfish
card.mcmobs.pufferfish.desc: Pufferfish are passive mobs found in oceans. They defend themselves by dealing damage and inflicting poison to nearby players and certain mobs.
card.mcmobs.rabbit.name: Rabbit
card.mcmobs.rabbit.desc: A rabbit is an uncommon passive mob and is a source of rabbit's foot, rabbit hide and raw rabbit.
card.mcmobs.salmon.name: Salmon
card.mcmobs.salmon.desc: Salmon are common passive aquatic mobs found in oceans and rivers. They are a reliable and nutritious source of early-game food when cooked.
card.mcmobs.sheep.name: Sheep
card.mcmobs.sheep.desc: Sheep are common passive mobs that supply wool and mutton and are found in many of the grassy biomes.
card.mcmobs.squid.name: Squid
card.mcmobs.squid.desc: Squid are common passive aquatic mobs that spawn in rivers and oceans.
card.mcmobs.tropical_fish.name: Tropical Fish
card.mcmobs.tropical_fish.desc: Tropical Fish are common passive mobs found in oceans. There are 2,700 naturally occurring variants. Using commands up to 3,584 visually distinctive variants can be spawned.
card.mcmobs.piglin.name: Piglin
card.mcmobs.piglin.desc: A piglin is a neutral mob found in the Nether. They attack players on sight unless the player is equipped with at least one piece of golden armor. Players can use gold ingots to barter with them for various items.
card.mcmobs.spider.name: Spider
card.mcmobs.spider.desc: A spider is a common neutral mob that has the unique ability to climb walls.
card.mcmobs.zombified_piglin.name: Zombified Piglin
card.mcmobs.zombified_piglin.desc: Zombified piglins are undead variants of piglins and piglin brutes that inhabit the Nether.
card.mcmobs.creeper.name: Creeper
card.mcmobs.creeper.desc: A creeper is a common hostile mob that silently approaches players and explodes.
card.mcmobs.drowned.name: Drowned
card.mcmobs.drowned.desc: Drowned are common underwater zombie variants that spawn in oceans and rivers, or when zombies drown. They are the only source of tridents.
card.mcmobs.endermite.name: Endermite
card.mcmobs.endermite.desc: An endermite is the smallest hostile mob. An endermite emits purple 'portal' particles, may spawn when a player throws an ender pearl and is useful for endermite lure traps.
card.mcmobs.ghast.name: Ghast
card.mcmobs.ghast.desc: Ghasts are large white floating ghost-like hostile mobs that live in the Nether which shoot explosive fireballs at the player.
card.mcmobs.guardian.name: Guardian
card.mcmobs.guardian.desc: A guardian is a pufferfish-like hostile mob that spawn in and around ocean monuments.
card.mcmobs.hoglin.name: Hoglin
card.mcmobs.hoglin.desc: A hoglin is a breedable hostile mob found in the Nether, and are a source of porkchops and leather.
card.mcmobs.husk.name: Husk
card.mcmobs.husk.desc: A husk is a variant of zombie that spawns in deserts. Unlike zombies, husks do not burn in sunlight.
card.mcmobs.magma_cube.name: Magma Cube
card.mcmobs.magma_cube.desc: A magma cube is a hostile mob found in the Nether. A magma cube behaves like a slime, but is stronger and more dangerous.
card.mcmobs.silverfish.name: Silverfish
card.mcmobs.silverfish.desc: Silverfish are small hostile mobs found hiding in stone-like blocks in mountains, strongholds, igloo basements and woodland mansions.
card.mcmobs.skeleton.name: Skeleton
card.mcmobs.skeleton.desc: Skeletons are common undead hostile mobs equipped with bows.
card.mcmobs.stray.name: Stray
card.mcmobs.stray.desc: Strays are variants of skeletons that spawn only in frozen, ice, or snowy biomes.
card.mcmobs.witch.name: Witch
card.mcmobs.witch.desc: The witch is an uncommon hostile mob that uses harmful splash potions as ranged weapons and beneficial positive potions on itself.
card.mcmobs.zoglin.name: Zoglin
card.mcmobs.zoglin.desc: Zoglins are undead hostile mobs created when a hoglin enters the Overworld or End.
card.mcmobs.zombie.name: Zombie
card.mcmobs.zombie.desc: Zombies are common undead hostile mobs that deal melee damage and attack in groups.
card.mcmobs.polar_bear_baby.name: Polar Bear (baby)
card.mcmobs.polar_bear_baby.desc: Polar bears are neutral mobs that live in icy biomes.
card.mcmobs.turtle.name: Turtle
card.mcmobs.turtle.desc: A turtle is a common passive mob found in beach biomes.
card.mcmobs.polar_bear.name: Polar Bear
card.mcmobs.polar_bear.desc: Polar bears are neutral mobs that live in icy biomes.
card.mcmobs.cat.name: Cat
card.mcmobs.cat.desc: Cats are tameable passive mobs that are found in villages and swamp huts.
card.mcmobs.fox.name: Fox
card.mcmobs.fox.desc: Foxes are nocturnal passive mobs that spawn commonly in taiga, giant tree taiga, and snowy taiga biomes.
card.mcmobs.mooshroom.name: Mooshroom
card.mcmobs.mooshroom.desc: Mooshrooms are mushroom-covered variants of cows exclusive to the rare mushroom fields biome.
card.mcmobs.mule.name: Mule
card.mcmobs.mule.desc: Mules are infertile offspring of horses and donkeys that, when tamed, can be ridden and equipped with chests.
card.mcmobs.ocelot.name: Ocelot
card.mcmobs.ocelot.desc: Ocelots are rare passive mobs found in jungles.
card.mcmobs.parrot.name: Parrot
card.mcmobs.parrot.desc: Parrots are rare tameable mobs found in jungles. Parrots can imitate sounds of nearby hostile mobs and can perch on the player's shoulders.
card.mcmobs.snow_golem.name: Snow Golem
card.mcmobs.snow_golem.desc: A snow golem is a snowman-like utility mob that helps defend against hostile and neutral mobs.
card.mcmobs.strider.name: Strider
card.mcmobs.strider.desc: Striders are passive mobs native to the Nether. They can walk/stride on lava and be saddled by the player.
card.mcmobs.villager.name: Villager
card.mcmobs.villager.desc: Villagers are passive mobs that inhabit villages, work at their professions, breed, and interact.
card.mcmobs.wandering_trader.name: Wandering Trader
card.mcmobs.wandering_trader.desc: The wandering trader is a passive mob that randomly spawns near the player. It can trade, making natural items more available, less dangerous to obtain, and in some cases, renewable.
card.mcmobs.bee.name: Bee
card.mcmobs.bee.desc: Bees are flying neutral mobs that live in bee nests and beehives. If provoked, bees attack in a swarm to "sting" the player and inflict poison.
card.mcmobs.cave_spider.name: Cave Spider
card.mcmobs.cave_spider.desc: A cave spider is a small venomous variant of the spider. They spawn and live in mineshafts.
card.mcmobs.enderman.name: Enderman
card.mcmobs.enderman.desc: Endermen are tall neutral mobs found in all three dimensions, which have the ability to teleport and pick up blocks.
card.mcmobs.iron_golem.name: Iron Golem
card.mcmobs.iron_golem.desc: An iron golem is a large strong neutral utility mob that defends players and villagers.
card.mcmobs.llama.name: Llama
card.mcmobs.llama.desc: Llamas are neutral mobs that can be tamed and used to transport large shipments of items.
card.mcmobs.wolf.name: Wolf
card.mcmobs.wolf.desc: Wolves are neutral mobs that can be tamed.
card.mcmobs.blaze.name: Blaze
card.mcmobs.blaze.desc: Blazes are floating hostile mobs found in nether fortresses, and are the only source of blaze rods.
card.mcmobs.phantom.name: Phantom
card.mcmobs.phantom.desc: Phantoms are flying undead hostile mobs that spawn when the player has not slept or died for three or more in-game days.
card.mcmobs.pillager.name: Pillager
card.mcmobs.pillager.desc: Pillagers are illagers armed with crossbows that patrol the Overworld, guard their outposts, and participate in raids, sometimes spawning on ravagers.
card.mcmobs.ravager.name: Ravager
card.mcmobs.ravager.desc: Ravagers are large hostile mobs that spawn in raids and attack players, villagers, wandering traders and iron golems.
card.mcmobs.shulker.name: Shulker
card.mcmobs.shulker.desc: Shulkers are box-shaped hostile mobs found in end cities. They hide in their shell to blend in with surrounding purpur blocks and guard the city's various treasures.
card.mcmobs.slime.name: Slime
card.mcmobs.slime.desc: Slimes are bouncy, cube-shaped hostile mobs that spawn deep underground in particular chunks known as slime chunks, or at night in swamp biomes.
card.mcmobs.wither_skeleton.name: Wither Skeleton
card.mcmobs.wither_skeleton.desc: Wither skeletons are tall variants of skeletons equipped with stone swords found in nether fortresses, which inflict the fatal Wither effect.
card.mcmobs.zombie_villager.name: Zombie Villager
card.mcmobs.zombie_villager.desc: Zombie villagers are variants of zombies that can be cured into normal villagers using golden apples while they are under the effect of Weakness.
card.mcmobs.dolphin.name: Dolphin
card.mcmobs.dolphin.desc: Dolphins are neutral mobs that live in non-frozen oceans, which grant a speed boost to players that swim near them.
card.mcmobs.skeleton_horse.name: Skeleton Horse
card.mcmobs.skeleton_horse.desc: Skeleton horses are undead variants of horses that rarely spawn when lightning strikes.
card.mcmobs.panda.name: Panda
card.mcmobs.panda.desc: A panda is a rare neutral mob that resides in jungles. Certain aspects of a panda's behavior and appearance vary depending on its personality.
card.mcmobs.chicken_jockey.name: Chicken Jockey
card.mcmobs.chicken_jockey.desc: Chicken jockeys are the rare appearance of a baby zombie, baby zombified piglin, baby zombie villager, baby husk, or baby drowned riding a chicken.
card.mcmobs.spider_jockey.name: Spider Jockey
card.mcmobs.spider_jockey.desc: Spider jockeys are the rare appearance of a spider being ridden by a skeleton.
card.mcmobs.vex.name: Vex
card.mcmobs.vex.desc: Vexes are tiny flying hostile mobs summoned in small groups of three by the spell-casting evoker.
card.mcmobs.vindicator.name: Vindicator
card.mcmobs.vindicator.desc: A vindicator is an illager equipped with an iron axe. Vindicators appear in woodland mansions and participate in raids.
card.mcmobs.piglin_brute.name: Piglin Brute
card.mcmobs.piglin_brute.desc: A piglin brute is a hostile and stronger variant of piglins that appears in all types of bastion remnants.
card.mcmobs.elder_guardian.name: Elder Guardian
card.mcmobs.elder_guardian.desc: An elder guardian is a stronger, larger variant of the guardian, and it can inflict Mining Fatigue. It is the largest aquatic mob in Minecraft.
card.mcmobs.evoker.name: Evoker
card.mcmobs.evoker.desc: An evoker is a spell-casting illager found in woodland mansions and raids, and is the only source of the totem of undying.
card.mcmobs.ravager_jockey.name: Ravager Jockey
card.mcmobs.ravager_jockey.desc: Ravager jockeys are formed when a Pillager, Vindicator or an Evoker rides on a Ravager.
card.mcmobs.skeleton_horseman.name: Skeleton Horseman
card.mcmobs.skeleton_horseman.desc: When a player comes within 10 blocks of the skeleton trap horse, lightning strikes it. When struck, the skeleton trap horse transforms into a skeleton horseman: a skeleton riding a skeleton horse.
card.mcmobs.ender_dragon.name: Ender Dragon
card.mcmobs.ender_dragon.desc: The Ender dragon is a gigantic flying hostile boss mob found when first entering the End. She is the largest naturally spawning mob in the game and is widely acknowledged as the final boss of Minecraft.
card.mcmobs.wither.name: Wither
card.mcmobs.wither.desc: The wither is an undead hostile boss mob that floats and shoots explosive skulls at players and mobs, that can only be purposely constructed by the player.
